.TH hsh 1 "January 2026" "Simple Shell" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.br
.B hsh
< file
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B hsh
program is a simple UNIX command line interpreter developed as part of the Holberton School project.

It provides a minimal environment to execute commands, search for executables in the PATH, and handle basic built-in commands.

.SH FEATURES
The shell implements the following features:
.IP \(bu
Display a prompt when running in interactive mode.
.IP \(bu
Read and parse command lines.
.IP \(bu
Execute commands found in the PATH or specified with an absolute/relative path.
.IP \(bu
Handle errors when commands are not found (exit status 127).
.IP \(bu
Built-in commands:
.RS
.IP exit
Exit the shell with the status of the last executed command.
.IP env
Print the current environment variables.
.RE

.SH USAGE
.TP
Interactive mode:
.RS
Run
.B ./hsh
and type commands at the prompt.
.RE
.TP
Non-interactive mode:
.RS
Pipe or redirect commands into
.B ./hsh
for batch execution.
.RE

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Run the shell interactively:
.RS
.B ./hsh
.RE
.TP
Execute commands from a file:
.RS
.B ./hsh
< script.sh
.RE
.TP
Print environment variables:
.RS
.B env
.RE
.TP
Exit the shell:
.RS
.B exit
.RE

.SH RETURN VALUE
The shell returns the exit status of the last executed command. If a command is not found, the shell exits with status 127.

.SH AUTHOR
Written by Joshua as part of the Holberton School simple shell project.
